'''Alice König''' lectures in Latin and Classical Studies and is Director of the Centre for the Literatures of the Roman Empire at the [[University of St Andrews]].<ref name=andrews>{{cite web|url=https://www.st-andrews.ac.uk/classics/staff/arw6/ |title=Dr Alice König, School of Classics |publisher=University of St Andrews |date= |accessdate=2016-12-09}}</ref>

König studied for her BA and MPhil at [[King's College, Cambridge]], and her PhD at [[St. John's College, Cambridge]].<ref name=andrews/>  She was the chair of the research network for ''Literary Interactions under [[Nerva]], [[Trajan]] & [[Hadrian]]'', a [[British Academy]] funded project.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://risweb.st-andrews.ac.uk/portal/en/projects/literary-interactions-under-nerva-trajan--hadrian(3bcf392b-340a-426b-b1b3-4c9877c7001f)/researchoutput.html |title=Literary Interactions under Nerva, Trajan & Hadrian - Research publications |publisher=University of St Andrews |date= |accessdate=2016-12-09}}</ref> König is a member of the Young Academy of Scotland established by the [[Royal Society of Edinburgh]].<ref>{{cite web|author=on 15 November 2016 |url=http://www.youngacademyofscotland.org.uk/about/relationship.html |title=Our Relationship with the Royal Society of Edinburgh |publisher=Youngacademyofscotland.org.uk |date=2016-11-15 |accessdate=2016-12-09}}</ref> She has appeared on the [[BBC Radio 4]] [[In Our Time (radio series)|In Our Time]] panel as an expert on "[[Agrippina the Younger]]" (2016), "[[Pliny the Younger]]" (2013) and "[[Vitruvius]]' [[De Architectura]]" (2012).<ref name=andrews/><ref>{{cite web|author=21:30 |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b074yzwk |title=BBC Radio 4 - In Our Time, Agrippina the Younger |publisher=BBC |date=2016-03-31 |accessdate=2016-12-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=21:30 |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b03kv0cl |title=BBC Radio 4 - In Our Time, Pliny the Younger |publisher=BBC |date=2013-12-12 |accessdate=2016-12-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=21:30 |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01d2kzx |title=BBC Radio 4 - In Our Time, Vitruvius and De Architectura |publisher=BBC |date=2012-03-15 |accessdate=2016-12-09}}</ref>

