'''Beqir Meta''' is [[Albania]]n historian and member of the [[Academy of Sciences of Albania]]<ref>{{cite web|title=ANËTARË TË RREGULLT TË AKADEMISË SË SHKENCAVE TË SHQIPËRISË|url=http://www.akad.edu.al/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=53&Itemid=88|publisher=Academy of Sciences of Albania|accessdate=20 February 2012|location=Tirana|language=Albanian|quote=Meta Beqir, Histori|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120302045032/http://www.akad.edu.al/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=53&Itemid=88|archivedate=2 March 2012|df=}}</ref> and director of the Institute of History. He published many works on [[Greek-Albanian relations]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Proceedings of the International Conference on MINORITY ISSUES IN THE BALKANS  AND THE EU |year=2007 |location=Istanbul |url=http://bal-kar.org/dosyalar/balkanminorities.pdf|editor=Mehmet HACISALİHOĞLUU, Fuat AKS|accessdate=20 February 2012|page=14 |quote=Beqir Meta has published several studies on Greek-Albanian relations.}}</ref> Meta is director of [[National Historical Museum (Albania)|National Historical Museum]] and president of the Scientific Committee of the [[Mother Teresa]] Museum.<ref>{{cite web|title=Scientific Committee|url=http://www.motherteresamuseum.org/comitatscient.htm|archive-url=https://archive.is/20120904181512/http://www.motherteresamuseum.org/comitatscient.htm|dead-url=yes|archive-date=4 September 2012|publisher=Mother Teresa Museum|accessdate=24 February 2012|quote=Prof. Beqir Meta Director of The Albanian National History Museum, where The Museum of Mother Teresa is located.}}</ref>

