[[File:Valenciennes-stage-bnf-ms-fr-12536-f1v-2.jpg|thumb|360px|right|alt=Passion play at Valenciennes in 1547|Stage Design for ''The Passion and Resurrection of the Savior'']] '''Hubert Cailleau''' (c. 1526–1590), was a French historical and [[Miniature (illuminated manuscript)|miniature]] painter and stage designer, who flourished at [[Valenciennes]]. There are some clever designs made by him, that now reside in the [[Bibliothèque nationale de France|National Library at Paris]], which were done for a [[Paschal mystery|mystery of the Passion]] acted at Valenciennes in 1547. He is famous for the illustrations of these sets, especially the frontispiece to ''The Passion and Resurrection of the Savior'' (1577), which are the most detailed surviving examples of such staging.
