'''Vladimir Vladimirovich Napolskikh''' ({{lang-ru|Влади́мир Влади́мирович Напо́льских}}, born 1 April 1963, [[Izhevsk]], USSR) is a [[Russia]]n [[ethnographer]], [[ethnologist]], [[ethnohistorian]], [[Finno-Ugric languages|Finno-Ugrist]] and [[linguist]]. [[Doktor nauk|Doctor of Historical Sciences]] (1992), Professor at [[Udmurt State University]]. Member of the «Societas Uralo-Altaica» since 2000. Corresponding Member of the [[Russian Academy of Sciences]] since 2011.
